<Layout title="About">
  <p>
    Welcome to Friends of Lums Pond, Inc., a dedicated nonprofit organization
    committed to the preservation and enhancement of Lums Pond State Park,
    Delaware's natural gem. Established in 2002, we are a passionate group of
    volunteers operating independently from Delaware State Parks. Our mission is
    to safeguard and enrich the park through meticulous needs assessment,
    transformative enhancement projects, effective public relations, and
    engaging educational initiatives.
  </p>
  <p>
    We volunteer, fund raise to support special park needs, educate, and
    advocate for our park. We are a registered 501c3 non-profit organization
    operating under a Friends agreement with the Division of Parks and
    Recreation. We adhere to Delaware State Parks Standards for Friends
    Organizations. All duly enrolled, participating members are considered
    Division volunteers.
  </p>

  <h3>Our Independence</h3>

  <p>
    We proudly stand as an independent entity, separate from State Park
    Management, which allows us the flexibility and freedom to pursue our
    mission with unwavering dedication and creativity.
  </p>

  <h3>Our Mission</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Preservation:</b> At the heart of our mission is the protection and
      preservation of Lums Pond State Park. We tirelessly work to ensure the
      park's ecological integrity and natural beauty are conserved for future
      generations.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Engagement:</b> Through educational programs, community outreach, and
      public relations efforts, we aim to foster a deep appreciation for the
      park's unique ecosystem and recreational opportunities.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Enhancement:</b> We are committed to enhancing the park's facilities
      and amenities, creating a welcoming environment for all visitors. This
      includes maintaining trails, improving recreational areas, and supporting
      sustainable initiatives.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Our Goals</h3>
  <p>Our collective efforts are aimed at achieving several key goals:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Public Awareness:</b> Increase public awareness and membership to
      strengthen our impact.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Park Beautification:</b> Maintain the park's natural beauty through
      landscaping efforts.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Trail Care:</b> Assist in the upkeep of multiuse trails for horseback
      riders and mountain bikers.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Cleanliness:</b> Ensure the park remains a clean and pristine
      destination for all.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Fundraising:</b> Raise funds to support the enhancement of park
      facilities and amenities.
    </li>
  </ul>
