      <h3>Park History</h3>
      <p>
        Lums Pond is a Delaware treasure, boasting the distinction of being the
        state's largest freshwater pond, covering 200 acres of the original 1790
        tract that now constitutes Lums Pond State Park. The park's rich history
        dates back to 1963 when it first became a state park. However, its
        origins trace to the early 1800s when the damming of St. Georges Creek
        and the construction of the C&D Canal created the iconic pond. Before
        this transformation, the creek flowed through a hardwood forest, serving
        as a hunting ground for Native American communities. The pond's waters
        powered the canal locks and a nearby mill.
      </p>
      <h3>Park Features</h3>
      <p>
        Lums Pond State Park offers a diverse array of features and amenities to
        delight visitors of all ages:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Scenic Trails:</b> Explore over 10 miles of picturesque hiking and
          biking trails.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Picnic Areas:</b> Enjoy shaded spots for picnicking and relaxation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b> Playground:</b> Children aged 5-12 can have a blast on our
          playground, divided into age-appropriate sections.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Nature Center:</b> Immerse yourself in the wonders of nature
          through year-round programming, including day camps, field trips, and
          public programs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Sports Galore:</b> Engage in various sporting activities, including
          volleyball, softball, horseshoes, cricket, disc golf, and horseback
          riding.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b> Boating:</b> Launch your boat, rent canoes, kayaks, paddle, or
          rowboats, and discover the park from its tranquil waters.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b> Fishing:</b> Enjoy year-round fishing in the serene surroundings
          of the pond.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b> Pavilions:</b> Host gatherings at one of our five pavilions
          available for rent.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b> Campground:</b> Experience the newly renovated campground offering
          sites with three-point hookups (water, electric, and sewer).
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Dog Park:</b> Let your furry friends roam freely in our off-leash
          dog park.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <hr />
      <p>
        Join us on this remarkable journey as we continue to champion Lums Pond
        State Park, creating a lasting legacy for generations to come. Together,
        we can make a difference in preserving the natural wonders of our
        beloved park.
      </p>
    </p>

